  "instructions": [
    "1. Sprinkle tofu with salt and mix with lime juice, soy sauce, minced garlic, and vegetable oil. Seal in a vacuum\u2011sealed bag or airtight zipper bag for sous\u2011vide. 2. Cook sous\u2011vide at 130\u00b0F (54\u00b0C) for 45 minutes. 3. While tofu cooks, mix rice vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch, and 2\u202ftbsp water to make a quick glaze; heat until thickened slightly, then remove from heat. 4. After tofu is done, pat dry, then briefly sear in a hot pan with 1 tsp sesame oil for 1\u20112\u202fminutes per side to develop a golden crust. 5. In a small bowl whisk peanut butter, soy sauce, lime juice, maple syrup, and 3\u202ftbsp water until smooth. 6. In a large bowl combine shredded carrot, sliced cucumber, chopped cilantro, sliced scallions, and jalape\u00f1o. 7. Toss the tofu pieces with the glaze and sprinkle with the peanut sauce; add the vegetables and mix gently. 8. Serve over shredded kale, top with roasted chickpeas and toasted sesame seeds, and drizzle any remaining peanut sauce. 9. Enjoy immediately!"
